==English==
===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''antiferromagnetism'''
#{{physics}} a [[phenomenon]], similar to [[ferromagnetism]], in which [[magnetic]] [[domain]]s line up in a [[regular]] [[pattern]], but with [[neighbouring]] [[electron]] [[spin]]s pointing in [[opposite]] [[direction]]s; materials showing this effect are either [[ferrimagnetic]] or [[diamagnetic]], and become [[paramagnetic]] above the [[Neel temperature]]
